    "41516000": {
      "title": "Determination of three acetylator phenotypes in a Mexican population using sulfamethazine metabolic ratio",
      "abstract": "Eighty-six Mexican young healthy volunteers received a 500-mg oral sulfamethazine dose. Urine was collected 0–6 h after medication and acetylated, and unchanged sulfamethazine were determined by the Bratton-Marshall method. The frequency distribution of acetylated/unchanged sulfamethazine, determined by probit analysis, appeared to be trimodal, allowing the discrimination of three acetylator phenotypes. The frequencies of rapid, intermediate, and slow acetylators were 28%, 42%, and 30% respectively, being consistent with the Hardy-Weinberg law."
    }
